It is noted that the Eqs. (8)–(11) are extremely non-linear and coupled ODEs. The exact/closed form solution of this system is difficult to obtain yet, therefore, we preferred for the analytical solution. The well-known analytical method, specifically, homotopy analysis method (HAM) is used to find the solution of the present boundary value problem. This approach is highly convergent, easy to understand, totally analytic, free from small/large parameters, and easy to program. This method has advantages over routine numerical methods in the sense that it is free of rounding of errors which arise due to discretization procedure. Additionally, it does not require large computer memory and time. The comprehensive procedure to implement this method is described by Liao [47] and here it is presented in the form of flow chart (see Fig. 2). This method is successfully applied in various non-linear engineering and industrial problems. Following initial guesses for velocity fields f′ηandg′(η)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
